  ('69ef8810-6fe1-5111-8653-7596f9f20d66', 'Age UK Cambridgeshire and Peterborough', 'Charity', 'Cambridge, Cambridgeshire', 'Cambridgeshire', 'https://www.ageuk.org.uk/cambridgeshireandpeterborough', 40, 1800000, 'FY 2024; Charity Commission total income', 5, 'Advice, befriending, home help and digital inclusion for older people — casework and volunteer coordination.', 'Medium', '2026-06-24', 'primary', 'Kathryn Buckland', 'Chief Executive', 'info@ageukcap.org.uk', '0300 666 9860', 'https://register-of-charities.charitycommission.gov.uk/en/charity-search/-/charity-details/1071007/full-print', 'https://www.ageuk.org.uk/cambridgeshireandpeterborough', ARRAY['older people'], ARRAY['advice','volunteers'], 'MEETING PREP — Age UK Cambridgeshire and Peterborough (Community & employment)

WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Welcome to Age UK Cambridgeshire and Peterborough — Age UK Cambridgeshire and Peterborough is an independent charity working in Cambridgeshire and Peterborough to offer support and services to older people. Find out more about us.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Cambridgeshire. ~40 staff; income on record £1,800,000.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Blend: training + VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Advice, befriending, home help and digital inclusion for older people — casework and volunteer coordination.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Community charities often run on CRM-lite tools plus spreadsheets. AI training and virtual assistance for coordination frequently land well when tied to visible admin pain.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
If the need is primarily a new CRM, position VAxAI as review and support around existing tools rather than a platform replacement.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
Age UK Cambridgeshire and Peterborough shows community & employment delivery with material admin load — Free up coordinator time across volunteers and bookings

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Free up coordinator time across volunteers and bookings
• Practical AI workshop for programme and outreach teams
• Review how reporting to funders is assembled each quarter

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

