WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Warrington Community Living seeks to support people with learning disabilities, older people and people experiencing mental health issues to lead their lives in a purposeful, healthy and enjoyable way as full and equal members of their local community. We do this through the provision of residential homes and supported living schemes as well as other forms of support in the community.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Bayshill Road, CHELTENHAM, GL50 3AT, Greater Manchester, Greater Manchester. ~95 staff; income on record £12,042,713.

