WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Free housing, employment and welfare legal advice with high casework, tribunal evidence and referral triage.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
Norwich, Norfolk, Norfolk. ~14 staff; income on record £580,000.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Workflow automation + training

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Free housing, employment and welfare legal advice with high casework, tribunal evidence and referral triage.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Advice charities process large enquiry volumes. AI for summarising case notes and drafting referral letters is attractive but needs strong data governance and staff training.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA alone cannot replace structured advice casework — automate triage templates and train staff on governed AI drafting first.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
Norfolk Community Law Service shows advice & advocacy delivery with material admin load — Reduce case note and referral letter drafting time with governed AI

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Reduce case note and referral letter drafting time with governed AI
• Workflow review across enquiry → advice → referral
• Train advisers on safe AI use with client confidentiality

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

