  ('d0ecf471-425d-5d05-9b69-070658a92f8d', 'THE FERRY PROJECT', 'Charity', '10a-14 South Brink, Wisbech, PE13 1JQ, Norfolk', 'Norfolk', 'https://www.ferryproject.org.uk', 25, 2297724, 'FY ending 2025-03-31; Charity Commission latest income', 5, 'Housing and homelessness services create tenancy, referral and contract-reporting administration. Community programmes involve volunteers, bookings, training registers and partner reporting.', 'Medium', '2026-06-24', 'primary', '', 'Chief Executive', 'OctaviaAdmin@ferryproject.org.uk', '01945 754080', 'https://register-of-charities.charitycommission.gov.uk/en/charity-search/-/charity-details/1075389/full-print', 'https://www.ferryproject.org.uk', ARRAY['housing','community'], ARRAY['housing','community'], 'MEETING PREP — THE FERRY PROJECT (Housing & homelessness)

WHAT THE ORGANISATION DOES:
Helping the homeless with love and support towards independence by providing personalised support and accommodation. We help to prevent homelessness by managing the Queen Mary Centre which provides a base for community organisations working with and for the local community. A central aim of the is to work closely with partners, including businesses, charities, churches and the public sector.

ORGANISATION CONTEXT:
10a-14 South Brink, Wisbech, PE13 1JQ, Norfolk, Norfolk. ~25 staff; income on record £2,297,724.

RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: Workflow review + selective VA

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Housing and homelessness services create tenancy, referral and contract-reporting administration. Community programmes involve volunteers, bookings, training registers and partner reporting.

CHARITY / SECTOR AI CONTEXT (use in conversation):
Many housing charities use housing management systems but still rely on spreadsheets and email for referrals, contract evidence, and partner reporting. AI for drafting support notes or summarising case updates is early-stage; staff often need training before tool adoption.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA alone is weak for real-time homelessness triage or statutory housing applications — automate referral logging and reporting templates first.

STRONGEST REASON TO CONTACT:
THE FERRY PROJECT shows housing & homelessness delivery with material admin load — Map referral-to-tenancy handoffs without replacing your HMS

HOW TO PRESENT VAxAI:
Position VAxAI as wraparound support: review existing systems, train staff on practical AI, and offer flexible virtual assistance for follow-through — not a CRM or case-system replacement.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• Map referral-to-tenancy handoffs without replacing your HMS
• Train staff on safe AI drafting for support notes with human review
• Reduce contract reporting prep with structured templates and VA follow-up

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• Which reporting, referral, or volunteer workflows consume the most coordinator time?
• What systems are in use today — and where do spreadsheets or email still carry the load?
• Has anyone been asked to explore AI, and is there a policy or governance concern?
• What would success look like in 90 days for the operations or programmes team?

